              "origin": "syntopicon",
              "content": "<p> Thus, according to the Old and New Testaments, Solomon was the son of David (Dāwîdh) son of Jesse (Îshê) son of Obed (‘Ôbhēdh) son of Boaz (Bô‘ēz) son of Nahshon (Naḥshôn) son of Salma (Shēlmâ) son of Amminadab (‘Ammînādhābh) son of Ram (Rām) (or Aram) son of Hazron (Ḥeṣrôn) son of Pharez (Phereṣ) son of Judah son of Jacob son of Isaac son of Abraham (1 Chronicles, 2:3-15; Matthew, 1:2-6; see 1 Samuel, 17:12-14). Muslim genealogists give a virtually identical Arabized rendition of Solomon’s paternal line as: Sulaymān ibn Dāwūd ibn Īshā ibn ‘Ūbīd (or ‘Awīd) ibn Bā‘iz (or ‘Ābir) ibn Salmūn ibn Naḥshūn ibn ‘Ammīnādab ibn Rām (or Aram) ibn Ḥaṣrūn ibn Fāriṣ ibn Yahūdhā ibn Ya‘qūb ibn Isḥāq ibn Ibrāhīm. The Bible does not mention the name of David’s mother, but the Talmud gives her name as Nizevet (Nîṣebheth) daughter of Adael. </p>",
